ll wp-image-810\" alt=\"GOOGLEBATTLEABBEYSCHOOL2\" src=\"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/01\/GOOGLEBATTLEABBEYSCHOOL2.jpg\" width=\"378\" height=\"283\" \/><\/a>September 2014 What a Month! A preview performance at the V and A Museum for their Digital Design Weekend. This was the first time we had partnered with The Met Office. \u00a0The Debut Performance of<span style=\"color: #000080;\"><strong> <a href=\"http:\/\/arrastre.org\/event.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #000080;\">[arra]stre<\/span><\/a><\/strong><\/span> at the Dome, Studio Theatre as part of the Brighton Digital Festival 2014. Following this we performed\u00a0at the Amex Stadium in Brighton to celebrate Women in Technology at American Express&#8217;CodeGirl Showcase Event. It might seem unusual that classical ballet might appear as part of a women in technology event but this is an unusual ballet.<\/p>\n<p>August was so much fun. \u00a0Lots of developing of the\u00a0<strong><a href=\"http:\/\/www.artofcs.org\/project\/light-up-with-gemma\/\" target=\"_blank\">wearables<\/a><\/strong>\u00a0for [arra]stre at the Brighton Digital Festival 2014. Wearables with dance performance costumes pose that added extra challenge. \u00a0The ballet dresses had 10 metres of chiffon on each one. Sewing electronics onto chiffon is rather difficult, especially all the electronics were done by hand. Each dress took anywhere between 4- 6 hours to sew on the electronics, 7 dresses in total. \u00a0All the wearables instructions and educational resources are available at our education site:\u00a0<strong><a href=\"http:\/\/www.artofcs.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.artofcs.org<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>In July we ran FireTechCamps Brighton Summer School which particularly exciting due to the face that the new MineCraft Course was of the Camp. \u00a0The venue for the camp was Sussex University which is is located at the North end of Brighton near the Football Stadium and across the road from Brighton University, Falmer Campus.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Apologies for the huge break in posts What have we been doing since June&#8230; WAY too much. That is still no excuse for not posting about it. Genevieve did have several major spinal surgeries and skin cancer to deal with&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[13,46,1],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/794"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=794"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/794\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=794"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=794"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.readysaltedcode.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=794"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}